
  SURFACE GRAMMATICAL ANALYSIS FOR THE EXTRACTION OF TERMINOLOGICAL NOUN PHRASES Didier BOURIGAULT Ecole des Hautes Etudes en Sciences Sociales et Electlicit6 de France Direction des Etudes et Recherches 1, avenue du G6n6ral de Gaulle 92141 Clamart Cedex France Tel : +33 1 47 65 50 64 ABSTRACT LEXTER is a software package for extracting terminology.
  A corpus of French language texts on any subject field is fed in, and LEXTER produces a list of likely terminological units to be submitted to an expert to be validated.
  To identify the terminological units, LEXTER takes their form into account and proceeds in two main stages : analysis, parsing.
  In the first stage, LEXTER uses a base of rules designed to indentify frontier markers in view to analysing the texts and extracting maximal- length noun phrases.
